# üîπ **Cross-Layer Dependencies & Flows**

```
Identity & Trust ‚Üí Procurement Design ‚Üí Marketplace Access & Discovery ‚Üí Bidding & Evaluation 
‚Üí Award & Contract ‚Üí Post-Award & Performance ‚Üí Lock-In & Behavioral Embedding ‚Üí Market Learning & Self-Correction ‚Üí Risk & Compliance ‚Üí Future-Proofing
```

* **Feedback Loops:**

  * Performance & trust feed back into evaluation & matching
  * Market transparency nudges behavior and improves efficiency
  * Learning curves enhance recommendations and pricing intelligence
  * Institutional memory reinforces buyer and supplier retention

* **Lock-In Mechanisms:**

  * **Behavioral:** Buyer habit formation (Logic 33), Supplier opportunity dependence (Logic 34)
  * **Institutional:** Trust scoring (Logic 25), historical records (Logic 32)
  * **Market:** Network effects (Logic 30), disintermediation resistance (Logic 39)

